the disembedding of a brazilian software page 1 2011 2012 clas lecture series presents the disembedding of a brazilian software dr roberto ierusalimschy associate professor department of informatics pontifical catholic university in rio de janeiro and tinker visiting professor stanford university march 6 2012 12 15 1 05 pm center for latin american studies bolivar house 582 alvarado row light lunch served las stanford edu lua is a programming language developed at the catholic university in rio de janeiro that came to be the leading scripting language in video games besides being used extensively in many other areas from set top boxes to photoshop lightroom in this talk professor ierusalimschy will relate the history of lua and how the language disembedded from its local roots to be inserted into a global open source culture he will also comment on the difficulties associated with promoting a project from a place considered peripheral in that culture roberto ierusalimschy is associate professor in the department of informatics at the pontifical catholic university in rio de janeiro puc rio and the leading architect of the lua programming language he is a researcher level 1 at the brazilian research council prof ierusalimschy was a postdoc fellow at the university of waterloo and a visiting researcher at icsi berkeley gmd berlin and uiuc urbana champaign and he is currently a tinker visiting professor at stanford
